sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor U as Usuario
    participant C as Cliente Angular
    participant A as auth.py
    participant S as AuthService
    participant R as UserRepository
    participant DB as PostgreSQL

    U->>C: Envia usuario, email y contrasena
    C->>A: POST /api/v1/auth/register
    A->>S: register(username, email, password)
    S->>R: get_by_email(email)
    R->>DB: SELECT * FROM users WHERE email = :email
    DB-->>R: Sin coincidencias

    alt El email ya existe
        S-->>C: 409 Conflict — "El email ya esta registrado"
    else Email disponible
        S->>S: hash_password() con bcrypt (salt aleatorio)
        S->>R: create(username, email, password_hash)
        R->>DB: INSERT INTO users
        S->>S: create_access_token(sub=user_id, username)
        S-->>C: 201 Created — access_token (JWT HS256, 24 h)
        C->>C: localStorage.setItem('access_token', ...)
        C-->>U: Redirige a /chat
    end

    Note over C,A: En login el flujo es identico,<br/>pero verify_password() compara el hash<br/>y devuelve 401 ante credenciales invalidas.
